  • Method Details

    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      This function sets the basic setting before the world controller has been received.
      It contains the default value for the button clicking music.
      It contains the default value for the button chosen status - not chosen.

    • initialize

      public void initialize(WorldController worldController)
      This function sets the basic setting for this page using the received game settings.
      It contains the initial setting for ball's m_Xspeed and m_Yspeed. It also allows the user to change the xpeed and m_Yspeed using the slider.
      Parameters:
      worldController - current game setting and information

    • ResetBall

      public void ResetBall(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent)
      This function allows the player to choose whether to reset the ball or not.
      It contains the changing for button's style.
      Parameters:
      mouseEvent - activated when the mouse click have been detected

    • SkipLevel

      public void SkipLevel(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent)
      This function allows the player to choose whether to skip the level or not.
      It contains the changing for button's style.
      When there are no next level, the warning message is shown and the button is disabled.
      Parameters:
      mouseEvent - activated when the mouse click have been detected

    • Exit

      public void Exit(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseEvent)
